  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1911</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The photograph displays the interior of the cinema's wooden construction. The photograph is taken from the position of the screen. The cinema floor resembles a restaurant with tables with bottles placed on them and chairs. A waiter is seen serving on the bottom left. A gallery offers seating for a bigger audience. The cinema hall is equipped with electric light. All the people in the picture, as well as the man on the gallery, are looking towards the camera.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The photograph was taken in 1911. The cinema was founded in 1909 by the Savić brothers Boža (1862–1927), Pera (1868–1925) and Svetolik (1874–1944).</ab>
